Druzzil Ro<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umanalow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manalow</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>knows that Warriors are Superior</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>7</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5:40:24 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.thegrid.net/chaotic78/Manalow.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Sitting as a Taunt</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">If it's a nasty fight and there's a mob that the enchanter has mezzed quite a few times, drained mana, slowed, etc.  plus the wizard snaring/rooting,  I will sit down in front of the mob while taunting, disarming, begging, making rude gestures, and insulting it's mother.  The first 2 seem effective, while the last 2 don't do much.  As far as begging I haven't seen an improvement one way or the other.  But I say go for it.  If there's a chance that it'll keep it off the casters do it.<br>
<br>
I personally think that begging only has any effect at all when the mob is not engaged in combat, similar to trying to give an NPC an item while it's engaged. Doesn't do anything.<br>
<br>
Dunno, I use it even for just the chance that it works.<br>
